&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.relexsolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/relex-greenhouse-banner-top.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1280&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;RELEX Solutions create cutting-edge supply chain and retail planning software. Within our platforms, we have the power and potential to increase adaptability, efficiency and sustainability in the consumer goods and retail value chain. Our impact is tangible; from sustainability and eliminating waste to delighting customers and delivering great tailored tech solutions, we’re curious and passionate challenge-seekers creating the future of retail today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Product Team&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RELEX Product team is pivotal in ensuring our continued growth. We build industry-leading products that fulfil the needs of world’s largest and most advanced retailers and manufacturers. Our products use advanced cutting edge technology like AI and ML while being user-friendly and efficient to use for the thousands of users we have. We have the happiest customers of our industry, and our customers couldn’t run their daily operations without RELEX. What’s more, through optimizing our customers supply chains, we save 11m kg of food waste every year. We are proud of our culture: we have a strong, talented, and ambitious team who doesn’t take themselves too seriously and has lots of fun together.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join us as a &lt;strong&gt;Director Product Strategy - Assortment &lt;/strong&gt;and this is some of what you and your team will be doing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director of Product Strategy for Assortment owns the what and the why for RELEX’s Assortment domain as an end-to-end business process within the broader merchandising strategy. They are commercially accountable for the domain’s ARR contribution, growth trends, win/loss patterns, and competitive positioning, while ensuring Assortment is defined not just as a product capability but as a strategic lever that connects customer planning, pricing, promotions, space, supply chain, and commercial execution. This is not a delivery role; the Director’s job is to define the problem space for end-to-end Assortment so clearly that engineering teams can operate with high autonomy within it, while also aligning strategically with other Product Strategy Directors to ensure Assortment is coherently integrated into RELEX’s wider merchandising vision and cross-domain value proposition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;KEY ACCOUNTABILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Outcomes owned — answerable if something goes wrong across the end-to-end Assortment process and its contribution to broader merchandising outcomes:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure RELEX is investing in the highest-value Assortment problems, evidenced by a prioritised strategy and explicit problem statements across assortment decisions, continuity and seasonal planning, merchandise financial planning, localisation, lifecycle management, and the upstream and downstream processes that shape merchandising outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive measurable ARR growth and retention in Assortment by ensuring RELEX’s assortment capabilities support stronger end-to-end merchandising decisions and deliver clear customer value across revenue, margin, shopper relevance, and inventory productivity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Position RELEX as a recognised authority in Assortment within a broader merchandising strategy, evidenced by stronger analyst, prospect, and customer recognition of differentiated value across assortment, planning, localisation, lifecycle, and connected merchandising workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure investment decisions and product priorities in Assortment are consistently informed by documented customer evidence, retailer workflow insight, and market si

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://www.relexsolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/relex-greenhouse-banner-top.png&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;1280&quot; style=&quot;max-width: 100%;&quot;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Who we are&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We solve the hardest problem in store operations. Ordering standard products is easy. Ordering the right amount of bakery, meat, dairy, fish, and produce — so stores stop wasting and stop running out — is not. That is what we build for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IDA was founded in 2023 as an applied AI company from day one. Acquired by RELEX Solutions in late 2025, we now own fresh store-level applications across the RELEX ecosystem. A small team by design, where everyone ships work that matters. We operate with short decision-making chains, real autonomy, and a culture where feedback is direct and impact is measured, without ego.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value people who are honest about what works and what does not, who take ownership of hard problems end to end, and who would rather build something tonight than schedule a meeting about it next week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Forward Deployed Engineer to be our first hire in the US, embedded in our largest and fastest-growing market. You will be the technical face of RELEX Fresh to US grocery retailers — combining engineering ability with real customer presence. You will own high-impact AI deployments from pre-sales to production, working directly with customers to ensure our solutions deliver measurable business outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engage across the full customer organization:&lt;/strong&gt; from C-suite to the shop floor. You own relationships at every level, from the executive sponsor setting the mandate to the store staff running your solution day to day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead requirements end-to-end:&lt;/strong&gt; gather, understand, workshop, challenge, and agree on what customers actually need, not just what they ask for. You are the person who makes sure we build the right thing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Write production code:&lt;/strong&gt; you will build and ship the core solution directly, and collaborate with central engineers to contribute improvements back into the product. Your code runs in live customer environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the outcomes:&lt;/strong&gt; KPI delivery on the customer side, solution performance, and SLAs. You are accountable until it works, and you know what “works” means in measurable terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep engineering experience in a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals and proven experience deploying ML or AI solutions into production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, or Azure) and modern data stacks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong business acumen, able to translate technical work into measurable financial impact and communicate it clearly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable managing ambiguity and taking full ownership of outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable using AI in your everyday work and developing AI tool adoption as an organisational strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What we offer&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility in how and where you work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Room to grow in a fast-moving global company with a strong market position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical benefits supporting work, family, wellness, and everyday life&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership, autonomy, and flat hierarchies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work that meaningfully reduces waste and improves sustainability&lt;/li&gt;
